The intermediate stations at , , Glasgow Central Low Level and  were reopened. A new station was created at .
The Argyle Line was further extended in December 2005 when a four-mile (6.4 km) section of the Mid Lanark Lines of the Caledonian Railway was reopened, serving ,  and .
Stirling to Alloa reopened on 19 May 2008, providing a passenger (and freight on to Kincardine) route once again after a 40-year gap.
