Ecologics(2010) &quot;A more critical interpretation is that after Macmillan named Marples as Minister of Transport, Britain&lt;U+2019&gt;s transport policy swerved to the right, and became motivated by the kind of conflict of interest that Thompson notes can be loosely regarded as a form of corruption (9). Actually, in this case it may well have been a rather tight form of corruption. At the time that he was named minister, Marples owned 64,000 of the 80,000 shares of Marples Ridgeway, a civil engineering firm that specialised in building roads&quot;↩
